ansforming the target into log space and focusing on price effects, the model may lose important scale information and struggle when converting predictions back to actual sales, leading to higher RMSE and MAE.\n","\n","In contrast, the baseline model uses historical sales patterns (e.g., rolling averages), which directly capture temporal trends, seasonality, and recent demand behavior. These patterns are often the strongest predictors of short-term sales, especially in retail datasets like this one.\n","\n","Overall, the baseline outperforms because it is better aligned with the structure of the data (time-series demand), while the regression model is more useful for interpretability (elasticity = -0.214) than for accurate forecasting."],"metadata":{"id":"mI5SpbP8Qm1-"},"id":"mI5SpbP8Qm1-"},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","results = pd.DataFrame([\n","    {\n","        \"model\": \"Baseline\",\n","        \"RMSE\": rmse_base,\n","        \"MAE\": mae_base,\n","        \"R2\": r2_base,\n","        \"Elasticity\": None\n","    },\n","    {\n","        \"model\": \"Regression\",\n","        \"RMSE\": rmse_reg,\n","        \"MAE\": mae_reg,\n","        \"R2\": r2_reg,\n","        \"Elasticity\": elasticity\n","    }\n","])\n","\n","file_path = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/Advance Machine Learning Project - Team 2/baseline_regression_model_results.csv\"\n","\n","results.to_csv(file_path, index=False)\n","\n","print(\"Saved clean model comparison results\")\n","print(results)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"K_N0d2BFv4aZ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776707392326,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":603,"user":{"displayName":"Andrew Brooks","userId":"05289463260007771788"}},"outputId":"da98d9c8-7e2a-481e-a8ae-fa0d3b8ac288"},"id":"K_N0d2BFv4aZ","execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Saved clean model comparison results\n","        model      RMSE       MAE        R2  Elas